PHOENIX Assurance together with Mauritius Union Assurance (MUA) has launched BimaPlus, new insurance aimed at commercial vehicle owners and transporters. The premium covers the commercial vehicle, goods and employees' all-in-one protection. Phoenix Chief Executive Officer, Ashraf Musbally, said yesterday in Dar es Salaam at the launching of a new product, the new innovation aims to expand their services in the country. Bima Plus will protect a transporter from daily risks associated with commercial operations such as road and personal accidents and damages caused by piracy or theft, and even weather damages. The insurance also offers recovery and towing services, riot and strikes cover, increased repair unit as well as loss of goods coverage which helps to avoid massive losses when faced with accidents. Furthermore, Bima Plus contributes to the loan repayment and loss of income while the vehicle is immobilized during repair after an accident. “We saw a gap in the market for commercial vehicle owners (transporters) who often face challenges while on the road resulting in huge losses and we believe as a responsible insurer, it is our obligation to offer solutions to our customers,” he said. Tanzania Insurance Regulatory Authority (TIRA) Eastern Zone Manager Mr Frank Fred commended Phoenix for establishing the new product in the market and believed will solve challenges for the transporters while Assistant Commissioner of Police (ACP) Meloe Buzema said the new product assured the securities of the businessmen.